723804f-a.text:
Universalist Church, Wadsworth Avenue at S.W. corner of 178th Street. This edifice was erected some time around 1920.
May 27, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
The New York Times of January 1, 1939 reports the sale of this edifice by the Universalist General Convention of Boston to the Mission Church, a Norwegian Lutheran Congregational body.

723805f-a.text:
109-113 Wadsworth Ave., at the N.E. corner of West 178th Street, showing the synagogue of the Congregation of Mount Sinai Anshei Emeth.
May 27, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
